"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-27-team-nigeria-dazzles-with-cultural-display-at-paris-2024-olympics-video\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The team Nigeria led by flagbearer, Tobi Amusan, defied the rain at the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympics.  The ceremony took place on Friday, with over 10,000 athletes on boats on the Seine River.  The teams embarked on a four mile boat cruise along the Seine River, passing through the structures.  During the nations' parade, the atmosphere reached a new peak of excitement when the team entered the arena in traditional attire that showcased Nigeria's diverse cultures.  In a now trending video on social media, Amusan led the team on their boat cruise, with Anuoluwapo Opeyori named the general captain.  The 2024 Olympics Games, featuring 10,714 athletes from 206 countries, will run from July 26 to August 11, 2024.  NPFL: Dogo promises to build formidable Kwara United squad  EPL: Mark him or not he will score - Semenyo hails Premier League best striker  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"